00:00:43.926 --> 00:00:44.426 A:middle
In case you're new

00:00:44.426 --> 00:00:46.056 A:middle
to the techonology,
new to the platform.

00:00:46.366 --> 00:00:47.386 A:middle
So let's do that real quick.

00:00:48.376 --> 00:00:50.826 A:middle
If were to define Auto Layout
in a sentence, which I've done,

00:00:51.306 --> 00:00:55.176 A:middle
is that it is a constraint-based
descriptive layout system.

00:00:56.126 --> 00:00:56.856 A:middle
That was helpful.

00:00:57.186 --> 00:00:59.236 A:middle
So let's look at
what that means.

00:00:59.586 --> 00:01:02.706 A:middle
So I have an interface here
and I want to describe it once.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:59.586 --> 00:01:02.706 A:middle
So I have an interface here
and I want to describe it once.

00:01:03.376 --> 00:01:06.756 A:middle
But I wanted to look good in
both portrait and landscape.

00:01:06.756 --> 00:01:09.486 A:middle
So what are some ways that
I can describe the interface

00:01:09.816 --> 00:01:10.546 A:middle
like I have here?

00:01:11.316 --> 00:01:13.996 A:middle
OK. One way I could do it would
be with the Hard-Coded Layout.

00:01:14.596 --> 00:01:17.116 A:middle
But, when I rotate my device,

00:01:17.406 --> 00:01:20.926 A:middle
if I keep my frame origin
fixed that, you know, 139,270,

00:01:21.366 --> 00:01:22.856 A:middle
then it's going to
be in the wrong spot

00:01:22.856 --> 00:01:23.906 A:middle
when I rotate my device.

00:01:24.836 --> 00:01:27.546 A:middle
So clearly, that's
not what we want.

00:01:28.656 --> 00:01:31.846 A:middle
So what's another what that we
could describe this interface?

00:01:32.596 --> 00:01:34.626 A:middle
Well, if I were to go
like to the white board

00:01:34.626 --> 00:01:36.966 A:middle
and like describe it to
someone, I might use terms like,

00:01:37.266 --> 00:01:40.516 A:middle
the control is centered
vertically in my container or,

00:01:40.516 --> 00:01:42.616 A:middle
to fix the distance
from the right edge,

00:01:42.616 --> 00:01:45.066 A:middle
and this is exactly
what Auto Layout is.

00:01:45.446 --> 00:01:47.056 A:middle
What Auto Layout is, is
it's taking this kind

00:01:47.056 --> 00:01:49.706 A:middle
of white board human
readable descriptions

00:01:50.036 --> 00:01:51.996 A:middle
and its codifying them
into these objects

00:01:52.166 --> 00:01:53.506 A:middle
that we call constraints.

00:01:53.836 --> 00:01:58.696 A:middle
Now, what the automatic
part is of Auto Layout is

00:01:58.696 --> 00:02:00.266 A:middle
that you provide the
constraints for us

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:01:58.696 --> 00:02:00.266 A:middle
that you provide the
constraints for us

00:02:00.456 --> 00:02:03.766 A:middle
and then we automatically
determine those frames based

00:02:03.766 --> 00:02:04.636 A:middle
upon the constraints.

00:02:05.296 --> 00:02:07.266 A:middle
Now, this is really
cool and really powerful

00:02:07.266 --> 00:02:07.996 A:middle
for a couple of reasons.

00:02:08.506 --> 00:02:10.826 A:middle
So, like I mentioned, first
of all, it's relational.

00:02:11.036 --> 00:02:13.116 A:middle
I'm just describing it how you
would describe it to someone

00:02:13.116 --> 00:02:14.386 A:middle
if you were just
explaining it to them

00:02:14.386 --> 00:02:16.386 A:middle
in the hallway or
on a white board.

00:02:17.296 --> 00:02:20.366 A:middle
And this relationship-based
layout is also going

00:02:20.366 --> 00:02:23.066 A:middle
to benefit us in other ways
too, especially when things

00:02:23.066 --> 00:02:24.766 A:middle
around us start changing.

00:02:25.196 --> 00:02:27.326 A:middle
This is the fun part
of writing code, right?

00:02:28.256 --> 00:02:30.356 A:middle
So, for example, let's talk
about metrics for a second.

00:02:30.866 --> 00:02:33.126 A:middle
I already talked about
rotation where the size

00:02:33.166 --> 00:02:36.346 A:middle
of container is changing
based upon the orientation

00:02:36.346 --> 00:02:39.666 A:middle
of our device or the think about
screen sizes, the difference

00:02:39.666 --> 00:02:42.326 A:middle
between a retina 3 and a half
inch and a retina 4 inch.

00:02:43.096 --> 00:02:45.566 A:middle
Or as we've been talking
about so far with this WWDC,

00:02:45.566 --> 00:02:48.576 A:middle
the differences between iOS 6

00:02:48.576 --> 00:02:51.596 A:middle
and iOS 7 were not only do we
have changes in the metrics

00:02:51.596 --> 00:02:54.376 A:middle
of controls like UI
switch and UI slider,

00:02:54.376 --> 00:02:57.466 A:middle
but we also have a great
new dynamic text feature

00:02:57.686 --> 00:02:59.046 A:middle
where the user can
actually change the size

00:02:59.046 --> 00:03:00.046 A:middle
of the font on the fly.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:02:59.046 --> 00:03:00.046 A:middle
of the font on the fly.

00:03:00.886 --> 00:03:04.886 A:middle
So, using Auto Layout and using
relationships to describe things

00:03:04.886 --> 00:03:08.666 A:middle
like spacings, alignments, equal
sizes, these are the things

00:03:08.666 --> 00:03:11.816 A:middle
that are going to translate
regardless of what the size

00:03:11.816 --> 00:03:13.416 A:middle
of the container is, so
the side of the control,

00:03:13.416 --> 00:03:14.476 A:middle
the side of your contents.

00:03:15.016 --> 00:03:16.366 A:middle
So, let's talk about content.

00:03:17.146 --> 00:03:20.896 A:middle
So, Localization is a really
common place that this comes up.

00:03:20.896 --> 00:03:22.886 A:middle
Now you guys are all
localizing applications, right?

00:03:22.886 --> 00:03:24.926 A:middle
I can just assume you are.

00:03:25.436 --> 00:03:26.476 A:middle
I'll take it by the yeses

00:03:26.476 --> 00:03:28.086 A:middle
and several languages
that you are, great!

00:03:28.676 --> 00:03:31.316 A:middle
If you're not, then this is a
great time to start doing so,

00:03:31.316 --> 00:03:33.526 A:middle
'cause not only it will
benefit you for Localization

00:03:33.526 --> 00:03:35.496 A:middle
but also all of the things
I've been talking about.

00:03:35.556 --> 00:03:38.316 A:middle
So let's talk about
expressiveness.

00:03:38.976 --> 00:03:40.576 A:middle
With Auto Layout,
you can do things

00:03:40.576 --> 00:03:42.896 A:middle
that just weren't
possible before

00:03:42.896 --> 00:03:44.826 A:middle
about writing a lot of code.

00:03:45.256 --> 00:03:47.816 A:middle
And as we all know, writing
code is writing bugs,

00:03:48.026 --> 00:03:51.166 A:middle
less code equals more
awesome most of the time.

00:03:51.286 --> 00:03:53.686 A:middle
So with Auto Layout, you
can express really powerful

00:03:53.686 --> 00:03:55.856 A:middle
relationships, and
if you're using Xcode

00:03:55.856 --> 00:03:57.886 A:middle
in Interface Builder, you can
express these really powerful

00:03:57.886 --> 00:04:00.256 A:middle
relationships again, without
writing a single line of code,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:03:57.886 --> 00:04:00.256 A:middle
relationships again, without
writing a single line of code,

00:04:00.566 --> 00:04:02.016 A:middle
and that is just a huge win.

00:04:02.586 --> 00:04:07.876 A:middle
So, as we've kind of been
saying so far with WWDC 2012,

00:04:07.956 --> 00:04:10.606 A:middle
this is a great time to
start adopting Auto Layout.

00:04:11.526 --> 00:04:13.206 A:middle
And so you might be wondering,
well, how do I do that?

00:04:13.286 --> 00:04:14.686 A:middle
I don't even know
where to start.

00:04:15.346 --> 00:04:17.745 A:middle
So, the first place to start
is with Interface Builder.

00:04:17.935 --> 00:04:20.755 A:middle
If you guys are using Interface
Builder, the first step that I

00:04:20.755 --> 00:04:22.656 A:middle
like to recommend is that
you go in Interface Builder

00:04:22.656 --> 00:04:25.366 A:middle
and you upgrade your documents
to start using Auto Layout

00:04:25.366 --> 00:04:26.596 A:middle
and you add constraints.

00:04:26.866 --> 00:04:28.916 A:middle
Now, let me pause here
and mention something

00:04:28.916 --> 00:04:31.156 A:middle
that I think it's
really critical to talk

00:04:31.156 --> 00:04:33.026 A:middle
about when it comes to some
of these new technologies.

00:04:33.676 --> 00:04:35.936 A:middle
Auto Layout can be
adopted incrementally.

00:04:36.186 --> 00:04:37.546 A:middle
It's not an all or
nothing thing.

00:04:37.546 --> 00:04:39.126 A:middle
You don't have to turn
it on for you whole app,

00:04:39.386 --> 00:04:41.666 A:middle
make it work all at ones, right?

00:04:41.666 --> 00:04:42.526 A:middle
We all have deadlines.

00:04:43.076 --> 00:04:44.456 A:middle
And, sometimes the task

00:04:44.726 --> 00:04:47.816 A:middle
of adopting a new technology
looks daunting giving it

00:04:47.816 --> 00:04:48.376 A:middle
a deadline.

00:04:48.846 --> 00:04:51.256 A:middle
But, with Auto Layout and
many of our new technologies,

00:04:51.486 --> 00:04:53.836 A:middle
with iOS 7 and OS X Mavericks,

00:04:53.836 --> 00:04:56.816 A:middle
is that you can adopt them
incrementally, bit by bit.

00:04:57.206 --> 00:04:59.396 A:middle
So, with Auto Layout,
the kind of granularity

00:04:59.396 --> 00:05:01.296 A:middle
for this is per view controller

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:04:59.396 --> 00:05:01.296 A:middle
for this is per view controller

00:05:01.296 --> 00:05:02.976 A:middle
or per Interface
Builder document.

00:05:03.666 --> 00:05:06.086 A:middle
And you can add just that one
piece in to use Auto Layout,

00:05:06.486 --> 00:05:08.376 A:middle
get it to work and
move on to the next.

00:05:08.376 --> 00:05:10.516 A:middle
You might only get two or
three view controllers working,

00:05:10.516 --> 00:05:12.536 A:middle
the place is what makes the
most sense then say, "You know,

00:05:12.536 --> 00:05:13.816 A:middle
I had a shift," great.

00:05:14.206 --> 00:05:16.266 A:middle
After the release, come
back, and keep moving on.

00:05:16.746 --> 00:05:19.206 A:middle
So I just want to make sure
that's really clear as we go on.

00:05:19.786 --> 00:05:24.886 A:middle
Now, a lot of us do things
outside of Interface Builder

00:05:24.886 --> 00:05:26.496 A:middle
with code, we add
extra subviews,

00:05:26.496 --> 00:05:27.806 A:middle
make little adjustments
here and there.

00:05:28.236 --> 00:05:31.176 A:middle
And this is the last part of
adopting Auto Layout is to go

00:05:31.176 --> 00:05:33.286 A:middle
to those places where you're
adding subviews dynamically

00:05:33.286 --> 00:05:35.976 A:middle
at runtime and you'll need
to update those call sites

00:05:35.976 --> 00:05:37.146 A:middle
to be aware of Auto Layout.

00:05:37.576 --> 00:05:38.586 A:middle
So previously, with the springs

00:05:38.586 --> 00:05:40.816 A:middle
and struts system you would
do things like setFrame,

00:05:40.816 --> 00:05:42.156 A:middle
addSubview, things like that.

00:05:42.726 --> 00:05:44.146 A:middle
You'll continue to
call addSubview,

00:05:44.146 --> 00:05:46.576 A:middle
but instead of calling
setFrame, now what you want

00:05:46.576 --> 00:05:49.556 A:middle
to do is either add constraints
or modify those constraints.

00:05:50.586 --> 00:05:52.696 A:middle
Now, the risk of being overly
complicated to quickly,

00:05:52.946 --> 00:05:54.786 A:middle
I'm going to point out one thing
that I want you to be aware

00:05:54.786 --> 00:05:55.906 A:middle
of as you're adopting
Auto Layout

00:05:55.906 --> 00:05:59.466 A:middle
and this is property called
translatesAutoresizingMaskInto

00:05:59.466 --> 00:06:00.016 A:middle
Constraints.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:05:59.466 --> 00:06:00.016 A:middle
Constraints.

00:06:00.536 --> 00:06:02.796 A:middle
What this does is it just
tells the system, "Hey,

00:06:02.976 --> 00:06:05.236 A:middle
I want you to help me by
generating constraints

00:06:05.236 --> 00:06:07.876 A:middle
that exactly mimic
the Autoresizing Mask.

00:06:08.556 --> 00:06:10.576 A:middle
So go back to this idea
of adopting incrementally.

00:06:10.886 --> 00:06:12.736 A:middle
In code, you can actually
get down to the level

00:06:12.736 --> 00:06:14.046 A:middle
of adopting it per view.

00:06:14.796 --> 00:06:17.396 A:middle
Now if you want to add your
own constraints, you're going

00:06:17.396 --> 00:06:19.386 A:middle
to want to have this
"Flag Off" turned

00:06:19.386 --> 00:06:20.816 A:middle
to "No," the default is "Yes."

00:06:21.436 --> 00:06:22.486 A:middle
If you use Interface Builder,

00:06:22.956 --> 00:06:24.506 A:middle
don't worry we'll
handle all for you.

00:06:24.726 --> 00:06:26.406 A:middle
But as you're adding
subviews and code,

00:06:26.406 --> 00:06:28.346 A:middle
you want to make sure you
turn that off if you want

00:06:28.346 --> 00:06:29.666 A:middle
to add your own constraints.

00:06:29.866 --> 00:06:30.226 A:middle
All right!

00:06:30.976 --> 00:06:35.446 A:middle
That was like the 3-minute crash
course into what Auto Layout is.

00:06:35.446 --> 00:06:37.566 A:middle
If you want to know more,
if you're still confused

00:06:37.566 --> 00:06:39.776 A:middle
at this point, you can go
check out these sessions

00:06:39.776 --> 00:06:43.226 A:middle
from the previous WWDC, there's
three great sessions here.

00:06:43.476 --> 00:06:44.716 A:middle
So if you're watching
the videos,

00:06:45.186 --> 00:06:46.706 A:middle
at the spacebar,
go check this out.

00:06:46.706 --> 00:06:48.866 A:middle
If you're on the
audience, well buckle up.

00:06:49.196 --> 00:06:50.186 A:middle
All right!

00:06:50.776 --> 00:06:52.756 A:middle
So let's talk a little
about kind

00:06:52.756 --> 00:06:54.516 A:middle
of how Auto Layout
has come to be.

00:06:54.516 --> 00:06:58.516 A:middle
So you may know in 2011, we
first introduced Auto Layout,

00:06:58.516 --> 00:07:01.456 A:middle
it was brand new for the
Mac, brand new for Xcode,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:06:58.516 --> 00:07:01.456 A:middle
it was brand new for the
Mac, brand new for Xcode,

00:07:01.686 --> 00:07:04.616 A:middle
and it was all about helping you
create Auto Layout interfaces

00:07:04.686 --> 00:07:06.896 A:middle
quickly, with the
Visual Format Language

00:07:06.896 --> 00:07:09.716 A:middle
and with the Interface Builder's
automatic constraint addition.

00:07:10.426 --> 00:07:11.466 A:middle
Now last year, it was all

00:07:11.466 --> 00:07:13.376 A:middle
about helping you build
Auto Layout interfaces

00:07:13.376 --> 00:07:17.006 A:middle
in more places, bringing
Auto Layout to iOS.

00:07:18.176 --> 00:07:20.476 A:middle
Now, it's been really cool
to get to work with you guys

00:07:20.476 --> 00:07:21.546 A:middle
over the last two years.

00:07:21.546 --> 00:07:23.246 A:middle
I've had a chance
to meet many of you.

00:07:23.636 --> 00:07:25.496 A:middle
And man, you guys are
doing some cool stuff,

00:07:26.026 --> 00:07:28.536 A:middle
like some really
custom cool stuff.

00:07:28.596 --> 00:07:30.046 A:middle
I just think it's awesome.

00:07:30.426 --> 00:07:32.836 A:middle
And so, what we're going to do
this year is we want to put you

00:07:32.836 --> 00:07:35.496 A:middle
in the driver seat when
it comes to Auto Layout.

00:07:35.976 --> 00:07:39.666 A:middle
And so, with Xcode 5 where we're
introducing a completely new

00:07:39.666 --> 00:07:42.676 A:middle
workflow for working with
Auto Layout in Xcode,

00:07:42.676 --> 00:07:46.106 A:middle
that will give you both kind
of broad painting strokes

00:07:46.356 --> 00:07:47.416 A:middle
for working with Auto Layout,

00:07:47.416 --> 00:07:50.446 A:middle
but also that really
fine-tune grained control

00:07:50.686 --> 00:07:53.226 A:middle
that will help you
accomplish and build those apps

00:07:53.786 --> 00:07:57.296 A:middle
that are just fantastic.

00:07:57.356 --> 00:08:00.166 A:middle
Now, as we talk about phases
of development, right,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:07:57.356 --> 00:08:00.166 A:middle
Now, as we talk about phases
of development, right,

00:08:00.166 --> 00:08:01.746 A:middle
we're adding features
that are going to help you

00:08:01.746 --> 00:08:03.006 A:middle
in every phase of development.

00:08:03.346 --> 00:08:04.596 A:middle
What are some of those
different phases?

00:08:04.596 --> 00:08:06.426 A:middle
Well, we all start here, right?

00:08:06.616 --> 00:08:09.276 A:middle
Initial Layout, and this is
just where you're dragging stuff

00:08:09.276 --> 00:08:13.036 A:middle
out for the first time, you
want to get stuff to show up.

00:08:13.486 --> 00:08:17.816 A:middle
At this point, I mean I'm not
really thinking about rotation

00:08:17.816 --> 00:08:21.486 A:middle
or localization, I'm just
pretty much concerned with--

00:08:21.486 --> 00:08:23.456 A:middle
can I remember how to
connect to a database

00:08:23.456 --> 00:08:24.896 A:middle
and can I populate my UI label,

00:08:25.306 --> 00:08:26.866 A:middle
that's pretty much what I'm
concerned at this point,

00:08:26.866 --> 00:08:28.796 A:middle
and getting things up and
running as quick as possible.

00:08:29.716 --> 00:08:31.526 A:middle
But then, eventually, I
do want start thinking

00:08:31.526 --> 00:08:34.336 A:middle
about how is my application
going to adopt when I rotate,

00:08:34.336 --> 00:08:36.265 A:middle
change devices, change
localizations?

00:08:36.596 --> 00:08:38.155 A:middle
And this is in an
Auto Layout world

00:08:38.155 --> 00:08:39.596 A:middle
where we start adding
constraints.

00:08:40.785 --> 00:08:44.116 A:middle
And then we all go through the
inevitable Debug cycle, well,

00:08:44.116 --> 00:08:45.516 A:middle
except the Apple 'cause
they don't have any bugs.

00:08:46.046 --> 00:08:47.566 A:middle
No, I'm just kidding.

00:08:47.566 --> 00:08:49.006 A:middle
So we all go through
that Debug cycle,

00:08:49.006 --> 00:08:50.946 A:middle
we identified problems
and fix them.

00:08:51.056 --> 00:08:53.976 A:middle
And then we kind of push
our interfaces often

00:08:53.976 --> 00:08:57.256 A:middle
to this Maintenance Mode, right,
I may make a few tweaks here

00:08:57.256 --> 00:08:59.296 A:middle
and there, but generally we're
not touching our interface

00:08:59.326 --> 00:09:00.946 A:middle
for probably quite a while.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:08:59.326 --> 00:09:00.946 A:middle
for probably quite a while.

00:09:01.396 --> 00:09:03.336 A:middle
And it's really important
in this phase

00:09:03.716 --> 00:09:07.356 A:middle
that when you're making those
single edits to your document,

00:09:07.466 --> 00:09:09.506 A:middle
that things aren't changing
that you're not aware of.

00:09:10.056 --> 00:09:12.786 A:middle
And this is last arrow that kind

