00:09:31.356 --> 00:09:34.096 A:middle
to help you start over
with some of your layout.

00:09:34.956 --> 00:09:37.116 A:middle
So what Tony and I are going
to show you today is how

00:09:37.116 --> 00:09:39.866 A:middle
with Xcode 5, we've added
features to help you

00:09:39.866 --> 00:09:40.776 A:middle
with each one of these phases.

00:09:40.846 --> 00:09:42.776 A:middle
So what we're going to do
is we're just going to walk

00:09:42.776 --> 00:09:43.956 A:middle
through each one of
these one by one.

00:09:43.956 --> 00:09:46.776 A:middle
So let's start with, at the
beginning, Initial Layout.

00:09:47.806 --> 00:09:50.106 A:middle
Now, again, this is just when
you're first adding views,

00:09:50.186 --> 00:09:52.436 A:middle
positioning, resizing,
I mean the stuff--

00:09:52.436 --> 00:09:54.106 A:middle
you guys got the stuff,
this stuff was easy.

00:09:55.396 --> 00:09:57.816 A:middle
And again, when you're working
in the space, you're not

00:09:57.816 --> 00:09:59.876 A:middle
yet thinking about
how it's going

00:09:59.876 --> 00:10:01.406 A:middle
to react the changes around you.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:09:59.876 --> 00:10:01.406 A:middle
to react the changes around you.

00:10:02.406 --> 00:10:05.216 A:middle
So, with Xcode 5,
when you add a view,

00:10:05.446 --> 00:10:07.486 A:middle
you get to add constraints
when you're ready.

00:10:07.486 --> 00:10:09.506 A:middle
Interface Builder is not
going to add any constraints

00:10:09.506 --> 00:10:17.906 A:middle
when you first add a view, you
get to decide when that's best.

00:10:17.906 --> 00:10:18.246 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:10:18.246 --> 00:10:20.136 A:middle
So then, you add a view, you
don't add any constraints,

00:10:20.136 --> 00:10:20.866 A:middle
and you build and run.

00:10:21.316 --> 00:10:22.496 A:middle
Well, what do you
expect to happen?

00:10:23.016 --> 00:10:25.616 A:middle
With Xcode 5, if you
haven't added any constraints

00:10:25.616 --> 00:10:29.156 A:middle
to the view yet, we will at
Build Time add fix position

00:10:29.206 --> 00:10:32.746 A:middle
and size constraints, so
that you can experiment very,

00:10:32.746 --> 00:10:34.626 A:middle
very quickly without
having to think

00:10:34.626 --> 00:10:36.206 A:middle
about constraints again
until you're ready.

00:10:37.616 --> 00:10:40.446 A:middle
Now, what this allows you
to do is this allows you

00:10:40.446 --> 00:10:42.916 A:middle
to separate your Layout
and Interface Builder

00:10:42.916 --> 00:10:44.136 A:middle
with your layout at runtime.

00:10:44.796 --> 00:10:47.576 A:middle
What you are dragging around and
resizing an Interface Builder,

00:10:47.576 --> 00:10:49.726 A:middle
could be independent of how
you're thinking about things

00:10:49.726 --> 00:10:51.616 A:middle
at runtime and then
you get to decide

00:10:51.616 --> 00:10:52.636 A:middle
when you want to synch that up.

00:10:53.186 --> 00:10:55.016 A:middle
You might say, "OK,
I want my constraints

00:10:55.016 --> 00:10:57.066 A:middle
to reflect what I have
in Interface Builder,"

00:10:57.066 --> 00:10:57.776 A:middle
or you might say,
" You know what,

00:10:57.776 --> 00:10:58.616 A:middle
I don't want Interface Builder

00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.096 A:middle
to reflect what my
constraints at."

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:00.096 A:middle
to reflect what my
constraints at."

00:11:00.096 --> 00:11:03.006 A:middle
And we've added features that
give you the precise control

00:11:03.006 --> 00:11:07.186 A:middle
over when you want to do that
and how you want to do that.

00:11:07.406 --> 00:11:10.336 A:middle
Now again, at this
point, I'm still thinking

00:11:10.336 --> 00:11:12.576 A:middle
