00:15:20.406 --> 00:15:22.336 A:middle
So why is it-- it
actually have a height,

00:15:22.336 --> 00:15:23.716 A:middle
I haven't add any
height constraint,

00:15:23.716 --> 00:15:24.526 A:middle
why does it have a height?

00:15:24.916 --> 00:15:26.656 A:middle
And this goes to one of
the concepts in Auto Layout

00:15:26.656 --> 00:15:29.616 A:middle
that is also really
powerful, which is the idea

00:15:29.616 --> 00:15:31.666 A:middle
of the intrinsic content size.

00:15:32.266 --> 00:15:36.636 A:middle
Most views like or most controls
rather like labels, buttons,

00:15:36.726 --> 00:15:40.586 A:middle
other things like that have a
size that is like they're sized

00:15:40.586 --> 00:15:43.916 A:middle
to fit size, think about it like
the size of the text of a label,

00:15:44.216 --> 00:15:45.706 A:middle
that's a great example
of something that--

00:15:45.706 --> 00:15:47.126 A:middle
the intrinsic content size is.

00:15:47.576 --> 00:15:50.796 A:middle
So from my button, the intrinsic
content size is the size

00:15:50.796 --> 00:15:52.036 A:middle
of the text, New Game.

00:15:52.186 --> 00:15:54.326 A:middle
So in this case, the
height there is showing me,

00:15:54.626 --> 00:15:56.296 A:middle
the height of the string game.

00:15:56.866 --> 00:16:01.526 A:middle
So, Control-Drag is
context sensitive.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:15:56.866 --> 00:16:01.526 A:middle
So, Control-Drag is
context sensitive.

00:16:02.026 --> 00:16:06.096 A:middle
So based upon the views I'm
dragging between and the angle

00:16:06.096 --> 00:16:08.336 A:middle
of the line that I'm drawing,
it will give me suggestions.

00:16:09.016 --> 00:16:11.756 A:middle
So if I'm drawing out a vertical
line and some horizontal,

00:16:12.166 --> 00:16:16.406 A:middle
you can see it gives me options
for vertical or horizontal--

00:16:16.406 --> 00:16:17.766 A:middle
vertical and horizontal
constraints.

00:16:19.076 --> 00:16:20.216 A:middle
We have a top space here

00:16:20.216 --> 00:16:22.296 A:middle
and then our horizontal
constraint is centering,

00:16:22.796 --> 00:16:24.996 A:middle
so based upon that line
that I've just drawn.

00:16:25.836 --> 00:16:28.266 A:middle
So I can pick a top
space and then I'm going

00:16:28.266 --> 00:16:29.516 A:middle
to draw one more constraint here

00:16:30.236 --> 00:16:32.756 A:middle
