00:16:33.186 --> 00:16:35.696 A:middle
Now, generally, you do not
want to add explicit width

00:16:35.696 --> 00:16:36.616 A:middle
and height constraints.

00:16:37.296 --> 00:16:39.246 A:middle
If you add an explicit
width or heights constraint,

00:16:39.246 --> 00:16:41.536 A:middle
then as the intrinsic
content size changes,

00:16:41.536 --> 00:16:44.376 A:middle
say when the font size changes

00:16:44.376 --> 00:16:46.796 A:middle
or the string inside
of it changes.

00:16:47.096 --> 00:16:49.086 A:middle
That control will
not change size

00:16:49.086 --> 00:16:51.446 A:middle
so you might get clipped text
or really awkward spaces.

