You can get an ambiguous
frame simply

00:37:58.006 --> 00:38:00.216 A:middle
by just not adding enough
constraints to your view.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:37:58.006 --> 00:38:00.216 A:middle
by just not adding enough
constraints to your view.

00:38:00.696 --> 00:38:03.326 A:middle
So, if you we take my example
here with my warrior imageView,

00:38:03.876 --> 00:38:06.026 A:middle
I've added three constraints,
one for the top space,

00:38:06.026 --> 00:38:07.386 A:middle
one for the height
and one for the width.

00:38:08.466 --> 00:38:12.156 A:middle
And together these three
constraints specify its size

00:38:12.156 --> 00:38:13.226 A:middle
and its vertical position

00:38:13.686 --> 00:38:15.876 A:middle
but they live its
horizontal position ambiguous.

00:38:16.296 --> 00:38:18.196 A:middle
And you can imagine if I
were to rotate the device,

00:38:18.396 --> 00:38:19.806 A:middle
the system wouldn't
know whether I want

00:38:19.806 --> 00:38:21.776 A:middle
to keep it centered
horizontally or keep

00:38:21.776 --> 00:38:26.216 A:middle
at the same distance
from the left.

00:38:26.466 --> 00:38:28.286 A:middle
Here's a slightly more
interesting example

00:38:28.286 --> 00:38:28.846 A:middle
of ambiguity.

00:38:29.256 --> 00:38:30.406 A:middle
Let's say, now I have two labels

00:38:30.856 --> 00:38:33.326 A:middle
with a horizontal spacing
constraint between them

00:38:33.526 --> 00:38:35.496 A:middle
and I have another
constraint between each label

00:38:35.496 --> 00:38:36.286 A:middle
at the edge of each container.

00:38:37.326 --> 00:38:40.006 A:middle
When I rotate the device,
the total horizontal space

00:38:40.006 --> 00:38:42.586 A:middle
in the container grows and
one of those labels need

00:38:42.586 --> 00:38:44.516 A:middle
to be stretched to fill
in that extra space.

00:38:45.386 --> 00:38:47.226 A:middle
Without any more information
the system doesn't know

00:38:47.226 --> 00:38:48.476 A:middle
which label I want to stretch.

00:38:48.476 --> 00:38:50.706 A:middle
So, my layout is
once again ambiguous.

00:38:51.346 --> 00:38:55.726 A:middle
So you can get conflicting
constraints

00:38:56.116 --> 00:38:58.476 A:middle
by over constraining
your view and it could be

00:38:58.476 --> 00:38:59.636 A:middle
as simple as this example here.

00:38:59.636 --> 00:39:01.866 A:middle
I've added two-- two
height constraints

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:38:59.636 --> 00:39:01.866 A:middle
I've added two-- two
height constraints

00:39:01.866 --> 00:39:03.626 A:middle
to my warrior imageView
saying it

00:39:03.626 --> 00:39:05.226 A:middle
to be two different
heights at the same time.

00:39:05.776 --> 00:39:08.876 A:middle
You can also get them in
slightly more subtle ways.

00:39:09.106 --> 00:39:11.586 A:middle
Let's say instead that I
have three constraints,

00:39:11.876 --> 00:39:13.796 A:middle
one for the top space,
one for the bottom space

00:39:13.796 --> 00:39:14.726 A:middle
and then one for the height.

00:39:15.366 --> 00:39:17.466 A:middle
And together they
add up to the--

00:39:17.576 --> 00:39:20.776 A:middle
the height of my screen
in landscape mode but then

00:39:20.776 --> 00:39:23.956 A:middle
when I rotate the device the--
the height of the screen grows

00:39:23.956 --> 00:39:27.306 A:middle
and now those constraints create
a conflict with the screen size.

00:39:29.656 --> 00:39:33.976 A:middle
The third type of issue is
misplaced views and this happens

00:39:33.976 --> 00:39:37.116 A:middle
when you resize or you
reposition your view

00:39:37.116 --> 00:39:39.586 A:middle
in Interface Builder without
updating its constraints.

00:39:40.356 --> 00:39:42.466 A:middle
So, let's say that now that
I have four constraints

00:39:42.466 --> 00:39:46.376 A:middle
that fully specify my imageViews
layout and it's not ambiguous,

00:39:46.376 --> 00:39:48.656 A:middle
it does not have any
conflicts but then I decided,

00:39:48.656 --> 00:39:50.576 A:middle
I really want to have
it centered vertically

00:39:50.576 --> 00:39:51.306 A:middle
in that container.

00:39:51.306 --> 00:39:54.506 A:middle
So, I just drag it down to the
center in Interface Builder

00:39:54.706 --> 00:39:57.166 A:middle
and not it's misplaced because
I still have that constraint

00:39:57.166 --> 00:39:59.556 A:middle
at the top saying it should
be 20 points from the top.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:40:00.396 --> 00:40:02.336 A:middle
So, interface builder
doesn't automatically update

00:40:02.336 --> 00:40:03.256 A:middle
your constraints.

00:40:03.296 --> 00:40:05.616 A:middle
And that's because it doesn't
know what your intent is.

00:40:05.616 --> 00:40:06.496 A:middle
It doesn't know whether you'd--

00:40:06.496 --> 00:40:09.326 A:middle
whether I want to update
that height constraint

00:40:09.326 --> 00:40:12.046 A:middle
and just stretch it down to the
middle or that I want to get rid

00:40:12.046 --> 00:40:14.966 A:middle
of it and replace it with a
vertical centering constraint.

00:40:15.456 --> 00:40:17.516 A:middle
So, rather than pick one
of those options for you,

00:40:17.516 --> 00:40:19.746 A:middle
it just makes it really easy
to update your misplaced view.

00:40:20.396 --> 00:40:24.986 A:middle
All right, so-- so those were
the three different types

00:40:24.986 --> 00:40:28.436 A:middle
of intermediate states and we've
added a ton of new features

00:40:28.436 --> 00:40:31.156 A:middle
to Xcode to help you quickly
debug and resolve these issues.

00:40:31.156 --> 00:40:32.506 A:middle
And the best way to show
you those features are

00:40:32.506 --> 00:40:36.176 A:middle
with the demo, so I'm going
to head over to Xcode now.

00:40:36.176 --> 00:40:37.376 A:middle
OK, let's start with
top one here.

00:40:37.686 --> 00:40:39.496 A:middle
I'll select and drag
up on its [inaudible].

00:40:39.496 --> 00:40:42.686 A:middle
OK, so when I did that,
a couple things happened.

00:40:43.846 --> 00:40:46.136 A:middle
First I got that dashed
rectangle and it tells me

00:40:46.136 --> 00:40:47.316 A:middle
that my button is misplaced.

00:40:48.126 --> 00:40:49.886 A:middle
And at runtime its
frame is going to be

00:40:49.886 --> 00:40:50.796 A:middle
where you see the dashes.

00:40:52.066 --> 00:40:55.476 A:middle
Also, over here my height
constraint turned orange

00:40:55.666 --> 00:40:56.836 A:middle
and I got this little badge.

00:40:56.926 --> 00:41:00.166 A:middle
So, that tells me that it's
currently 32 point shorter

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:40:56.926 --> 00:41:00.166 A:middle
So, that tells me that it's
currently 32 point shorter

00:41:00.166 --> 00:41:01.706 A:middle
than the height of the
button in the canvas

00:41:02.126 --> 00:41:03.806 A:middle
and that it explains
why it's misplaced.

00:41:03.906 --> 00:41:05.556 A:middle
I need to update that
height constraint.

00:41:06.406 --> 00:41:09.036 A:middle
So, I could do that by selecting
the height constraint and going

00:41:09.036 --> 00:41:11.236 A:middle
over the inspector and adding
32 points to its value.

00:41:11.776 --> 00:41:13.826 A:middle
But this is a very
common type of operation.

00:41:13.826 --> 00:41:15.136 A:middle
So, we've got a short
cut for doing that.

00:41:15.616 --> 00:41:20.796 A:middle
So instead, I'm going to head
down here, and what I'm going

00:41:20.796 --> 00:41:23.776 A:middle
to do is use this command
here, Update Constraints.

00:41:24.786 --> 00:41:27.506 A:middle
So, this looks at your
selected view, and it looks

00:41:27.506 --> 00:41:28.926 A:middle
at all the constraints
that are touching it,

00:41:28.926 --> 00:41:30.366 A:middle
and it updates their values

00:41:30.366 --> 00:41:31.786 A:middle
to reflect its current
frame in the canvas.

00:41:32.656 --> 00:41:35.086 A:middle
So when I click that, it's going
to update my height constraint

00:41:35.086 --> 00:41:38.356 A:middle
over there, and you can see
now it's no longer misplaced.

00:41:38.756 --> 00:41:43.896 A:middle
All right, let's move
on to the other buttons.

00:41:43.896 --> 00:41:46.956 A:middle
I could follow the exact
same, the back exacts in step,

00:41:46.956 --> 00:41:49.906 A:middle
so I could just resize them and
update their height constraints.

00:41:50.266 --> 00:41:52.266 A:middle
But then I'd have to make sure
I made them all exactly the

00:41:52.266 --> 00:41:52.786 A:middle
same height.

00:41:53.416 --> 00:41:54.166 A:middle
So instead, what I'm going

00:41:54.166 --> 00:41:55.726 A:middle
to do is create an Equal
Heights constraint.

00:41:55.876 --> 00:42:00.766 A:middle
I'm going to Control-Drag down
here and choose Equal Heights.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:41:55.876 --> 00:42:00.766 A:middle
I'm going to Control-Drag down
here and choose Equal Heights.

00:42:00.846 --> 00:42:03.906 A:middle
So, this constraint is going to
make the system enforce the fact

00:42:03.906 --> 00:42:04.936 A:middle
that they all have
the same height.

00:42:05.506 --> 00:42:07.826 A:middle
So, I choose that,
I get a conflict.

00:42:08.496 --> 00:42:10.676 A:middle
The reason why I got a conflict
is I still have this old height

00:42:10.676 --> 00:42:12.736 A:middle
constraint here,
and it's telling me

00:42:12.736 --> 00:42:15.086 A:middle
that it's 43 points tall.

00:42:15.426 --> 00:42:18.276 A:middle
So, now I have that constraint
saying it should be 43 points,

00:42:18.636 --> 00:42:20.776 A:middle
and I also went and added
that Equal Heights constraint,

00:42:21.026 --> 00:42:21.956 A:middle
saying it should
be the same height

00:42:21.956 --> 00:42:24.016 A:middle
as the Top button
which is 75 points.

00:42:24.956 --> 00:42:26.746 A:middle
So, I need to delete
one of these constraints

00:42:26.746 --> 00:42:27.666 A:middle
to resolve this conflict.

00:42:28.666 --> 00:42:30.746 A:middle
I'm just going to delete
that old height constraint

00:42:30.796 --> 00:42:35.286 A:middle
because it's-- I don't
need that anymore.

00:42:35.376 --> 00:42:36.396 A:middle
All right, so I did that.

00:42:36.396 --> 00:42:41.086 A:middle
I got rid of the conflict, but
now my button is still misplaced

00:42:41.086 --> 00:42:44.486 A:middle
because its-- the frame in
the canvas hasn't-- has--

00:42:44.486 --> 00:42:46.856 A:middle
is no longer reflecting that
Equal Heights constraint.

00:42:48.316 --> 00:42:50.366 A:middle
So, I could resolve
this by going

00:42:50.366 --> 00:42:52.076 A:middle
into the button's size inspector

00:42:52.546 --> 00:42:54.926 A:middle
and adding 32 points
to its height.

00:42:55.026 --> 00:42:58.036 A:middle
But again, this is a very
common type of operation,

00:42:58.036 --> 00:42:59.696 A:middle
so we've added another
shortcut for doing that.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:43:00.126 --> 00:43:02.036 A:middle
And that's over here in
the bottom of the canvas,

00:43:02.346 --> 00:43:04.136 A:middle
back in our Auto Layout menu.

00:43:04.906 --> 00:43:06.816 A:middle
So this time, I'm going
to choose Update Frames.

00:43:08.036 --> 00:43:11.556 A:middle
Update Frames resizes and
repositions your views according

00:43:11.556 --> 00:43:13.466 A:middle
to their constraints,
so it makes their frame

00:43:13.466 --> 00:43:15.346 A:middle
in the canvas match
their frame at runtime.

00:43:15.346 --> 00:43:21.046 A:middle
When I choose that, now my
button is no longer misplaced

00:43:21.046 --> 00:43:25.296 A:middle
and it's resized
just like I wanted.

00:43:25.386 --> 00:43:26.886 A:middle
All right, let's do the same
thing for the Middle button.

00:43:26.886 --> 00:43:29.166 A:middle
I'm going to start by deleting
its height constraints,

00:43:29.166 --> 00:43:31.406 A:middle
so it doesn't-- so I don't
run into that conflict.

00:43:31.796 --> 00:43:35.186 A:middle
And I'm going to
Control-Drag down and add

00:43:35.186 --> 00:43:38.976 A:middle
that Equal Heights constraint.

00:43:38.976 --> 00:43:41.326 A:middle
OK, so now my Middle
button is misplaced

00:43:42.056 --> 00:43:46.186 A:middle
because I have an updated site
and by virtue of growing taller,

00:43:46.186 --> 00:43:47.856 A:middle
it's going to push apart
those other two buttons.

00:43:48.106 --> 00:43:49.956 A:middle
So now actually if I
select these buttons,

00:43:49.956 --> 00:43:51.536 A:middle
you can see they're
all misplaced.

00:43:51.536 --> 00:43:53.446 A:middle
They're all either in the wrong
position or have the wrong set.

00:43:54.146 --> 00:43:56.826 A:middle
So, let's go back to the
menu and update their frames.

00:43:59.436 --> 00:44:02.336 A:middle
This time, I want to
point out the fact

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:43:59.436 --> 00:44:02.336 A:middle
This time, I want to
point out the fact

00:44:02.496 --> 00:44:04.726 A:middle
that this menu is
divided into two halves,

00:44:05.056 --> 00:44:05.946 A:middle
so we're zooming down here.

00:44:06.516 --> 00:44:08.596 A:middle
It's divided into two halves.

00:44:08.746 --> 00:44:10.826 A:middle
On the top half, we
have command that apply

00:44:10.826 --> 00:44:13.446 A:middle
to the currently selected
view, and on the bottom half,

00:44:13.916 --> 00:44:15.996 A:middle
we have commands that
apply to all views

00:44:15.996 --> 00:44:17.856 A:middle
in the current scene
in your story board.

00:44:18.826 --> 00:44:23.226 A:middle
So in this case, I want to
choose update all the frames

00:44:23.316 --> 00:44:24.796 A:middle
in my splash screen
view controller.

00:44:24.796 --> 00:44:26.476 A:middle
So that's going to apply
that update frames command

00:44:26.476 --> 00:44:27.496 A:middle
to all three buttons at once.

00:44:28.426 --> 00:44:33.456 A:middle
When I do that, it resizes or
repositions all three buttons,

00:44:33.456 --> 00:44:34.756 A:middle
and now they're not
misplaced anymore.

00:44:35.516 --> 00:44:41.696 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:44:42.196 --> 00:44:43.496 A:middle
OK, so you just saw a
couple different ways

00:44:43.496 --> 00:44:44.576 A:middle
to resolve misplaced views.

00:44:44.916 --> 00:44:46.966 A:middle
Now, I'm going to move
on to ambiguous frames.

00:44:47.666 --> 00:44:48.846 A:middle
And to that, I'm going
to head over here

00:44:48.846 --> 00:44:50.186 A:middle
to my load game view controller.

00:44:50.756 --> 00:44:54.946 A:middle
OK, so this is a
table view controller,

00:44:54.946 --> 00:44:56.256 A:middle
and it has a prototype cell.

00:44:57.046 --> 00:44:59.166 A:middle
That prototype cell is going
to get reused at runtime

00:44:59.166 --> 00:45:01.306 A:middle
for every saved game
that the player can load.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:44:59.166 --> 00:45:01.306 A:middle
for every saved game
that the player can load.

00:45:02.166 --> 00:45:03.806 A:middle
And the cell has a
couple of labels here,

00:45:03.806 --> 00:45:07.796 A:middle
and those represent the name,
the name of my character

00:45:07.796 --> 00:45:09.426 A:middle
and the date that I last
played with that character.

00:45:10.336 --> 00:45:11.326 A:middle
And when I select these labels,

00:45:11.326 --> 00:45:13.336 A:middle
you can see they currently don't
have any constraints on them,

00:45:13.596 --> 00:45:16.226 A:middle
so at runtime, they're going to
have fixed sizes, fixed frames,

00:45:16.226 --> 00:45:17.696 A:middle
fixed positions and sizes.

00:45:18.556 --> 00:45:21.706 A:middle
So, I want to hit Build and Run
now, and so you can take a look

00:45:22.246 --> 00:45:23.736 A:middle
at this table view without,

00:45:23.736 --> 00:45:24.966 A:middle
before I start adding
constraints.

00:45:24.966 --> 00:45:30.786 A:middle
All right, so here's our splash
screen, I'm just going to tap

00:45:30.786 --> 00:45:32.936 A:middle
on Load Game, and
here's our table view.

00:45:32.936 --> 00:45:35.516 A:middle
And so you can see all the
labels are getting clipped,

00:45:35.516 --> 00:45:37.816 A:middle
and that's because
those static sizes

00:45:37.816 --> 00:45:39.456 A:middle
that we gave them
are just too short

00:45:39.456 --> 00:45:41.126 A:middle
to fit their content at runtime.

00:45:41.696 --> 00:45:43.886 A:middle
So, let's go back to IB
and add some constraints

00:45:43.886 --> 00:45:44.986 A:middle
to let them grow dynamically.

00:45:48.676 --> 00:45:50.386 A:middle
[pause] Let's start with
our date label here.

00:45:50.586 --> 00:45:52.636 A:middle
I'm just going to
Control-Drag over

00:45:52.666 --> 00:45:55.166 A:middle
and add a leading space
constraint, that's just going

00:45:55.166 --> 00:45:56.346 A:middle
to pin it to the left
side of the cell.

00:45:56.896 --> 00:46:00.396 A:middle
And when I did that, it gave
me an orange constraint.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:45:56.896 --> 00:46:00.396 A:middle
And when I did that, it gave
me an orange constraint.

00:46:00.916 --> 00:46:04.676 A:middle
It's orange because my
date label is ambiguous,

00:46:05.466 --> 00:46:11.366 A:middle
and I can also see this at
the top of the canvas up here

00:46:11.366 --> 00:46:14.806 A:middle
in the-- in our mini navigator.

00:46:15.056 --> 00:46:16.756 A:middle
So, this button here
is a mini navigator

00:46:16.756 --> 00:46:17.896 A:middle
and it gives you a quick summary

00:46:17.896 --> 00:46:19.656 A:middle
of all the unresolved
issues in your document.

00:46:19.946 --> 00:46:22.826 A:middle
So when I click that, it tells
me the vertical position is

00:46:22.826 --> 00:46:23.966 A:middle
ambiguous for my date label.

00:46:24.446 --> 00:46:28.836 A:middle
So, that makes sense because
we've only added a single

00:46:29.126 --> 00:46:30.866 A:middle
horizontal constraint.

00:46:30.866 --> 00:46:32.286 A:middle
So, we need to add
more constraints

00:46:32.286 --> 00:46:33.906 A:middle
to fully specify its position.

00:46:34.296 --> 00:46:37.116 A:middle
I could keep adding
constraints to each of my labels

00:46:37.116 --> 00:46:38.686 A:middle
until they're unambiguous,
but instead I'm going

00:46:38.686 --> 00:46:39.696 A:middle
to use another shortcut.

00:46:40.006 --> 00:46:42.806 A:middle
So, when I head back to this
menu, and this time I'm going

00:46:42.806 --> 00:46:44.946 A:middle
to choose Add Missing
constraints

00:46:44.946 --> 00:46:46.006 A:middle
and Load Game Table at the cell.

00:46:46.236 --> 00:46:46.926 A:middle
So, it's going to apply

00:46:46.926 --> 00:46:49.236 A:middle
that same Add Missing
constraints command

00:46:49.236 --> 00:46:51.556 A:middle
that Kevin showed you, and
it's going to apply it to all--

00:46:51.556 --> 00:46:52.586 A:middle
both my labels at once.

00:46:52.816 --> 00:46:56.326 A:middle
So when I choose that,
my constraints turn blue

00:46:56.486 --> 00:46:58.416 A:middle
and you can see now I
have four constraints.

00:46:59.086 --> 00:47:02.186 A:middle
And these are enough to
fully specify the layout

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:46:59.086 --> 00:47:02.186 A:middle
And these are enough to
fully specify the layout

00:47:02.186 --> 00:47:04.076 A:middle
of my two labels.

00:47:05.606 --> 00:47:07.426 A:middle
So, I got a leading
space constraint.

00:47:07.426 --> 00:47:08.656 A:middle
I got a top space constraint.

00:47:08.856 --> 00:47:11.126 A:middle
I got a baseline alignment
constraint that's going

00:47:11.126 --> 00:47:12.296 A:middle
to align the two
labels vertically.

00:47:12.656 --> 00:47:16.016 A:middle
And I got a little horizontal
spacing constraint between them.

00:47:16.406 --> 00:47:19.216 A:middle
So, you might be wondering
why I didn't get any with

00:47:19.216 --> 00:47:21.726 A:middle
or height constraints, and
that gets back to the idea

00:47:21.726 --> 00:47:24.646 A:middle
of this intrinsic content
size that we get from UILabel.

00:47:24.646 --> 00:47:26.876 A:middle
So at runtime, it's going
to infer its size based

00:47:26.876 --> 00:47:29.926 A:middle
on its content and that's
going to let it grow and resize

00:47:29.926 --> 00:47:32.286 A:middle
and our labels won't
be clipped anymore.

00:47:33.156 --> 00:47:33.976 A:middle
So, let's see what
that looks like.

00:47:34.516 --> 00:47:41.576 A:middle
[Pause]

00:47:42.076 --> 00:47:45.316 A:middle
All right, so now our labels
are no longer getting clipped.

00:47:46.206 --> 00:47:49.026 A:middle
The first two cells look
great and the third cell,

00:47:49.026 --> 00:47:50.476 A:middle
I have a character with
a really long name,

00:47:50.876 --> 00:47:53.206 A:middle
and that's just running right
off the edge of the cell,

00:47:53.986 --> 00:47:56.986 A:middle
and it's actually occluding
my disclosure indicator here.

00:47:58.166 --> 00:48:00.126 A:middle
So, what I want to do
is add a little padding

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:47:58.166 --> 00:48:00.126 A:middle
So, what I want to do
is add a little padding

00:48:00.126 --> 00:48:01.486 A:middle
on the right side, so that

00:48:01.486 --> 00:48:04.036 A:middle
that name label gets
clipped before it runs

00:48:04.036 --> 00:48:05.956 A:middle
over in the disclosure
indicator, so let's do that.

00:48:05.996 --> 00:48:12.096 A:middle
All right, so I'll
just control-drag over

00:48:12.096 --> 00:48:13.406 A:middle
and choose trailing space.

00:48:13.986 --> 00:48:16.296 A:middle
And that gave me a bit
more padding that I wanted,

00:48:16.296 --> 00:48:19.766 A:middle
so I'm just going to double
click it and choose 40 points.

00:48:21.076 --> 00:48:22.736 A:middle
So I did that, I
got a new issue.

00:48:23.956 --> 00:48:25.226 A:middle
This is a new type of ambiguity.

00:48:26.366 --> 00:48:27.796 A:middle
And it's ambiguous
because if you add

00:48:27.796 --> 00:48:30.436 A:middle
up the 3 horizontal constraints
we have and the widths

00:48:30.436 --> 00:48:32.276 A:middle
of the two labels,
it doesn't quite add

00:48:32.276 --> 00:48:33.386 A:middle
up to the full width
of the cell.

00:48:34.016 --> 00:48:36.766 A:middle
And so one of those labels
needs to be stretched to fill

00:48:36.766 --> 00:48:39.136 A:middle
in the extra space, and I
haven't told Interface Builder

00:48:39.136 --> 00:48:41.186 A:middle
which one I want to resize yet.

00:48:42.016 --> 00:48:44.876 A:middle
For situations like this when
you encounter a new issue,

00:48:44.996 --> 00:48:46.656 A:middle
and maybe you're not
familiar with it,

00:48:46.656 --> 00:48:47.916 A:middle
you're not sure how
to resolve it.

00:48:47.916 --> 00:48:49.766 A:middle
You want to get some
suggestions on how to fix it.

00:48:50.116 --> 00:48:52.396 A:middle
You can always head over to the
Interface Builder outline view,

00:48:52.486 --> 00:48:53.396 A:middle
and get some information.

00:48:53.716 --> 00:48:55.186 A:middle
So, let's do that.

00:48:57.796 --> 00:48:59.846 A:middle
If you look here by my
load game view controller,

00:48:59.846 --> 00:49:01.876 A:middle
you can see I have
this button here.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:48:59.846 --> 00:49:01.876 A:middle
you can see I have
this button here.

00:49:02.166 --> 00:49:04.736 A:middle
And that's-- that indicates

00:49:04.846 --> 00:49:07.146 A:middle
that I have unresolved Auto
Layout issues in that scene.

00:49:07.886 --> 00:49:10.796 A:middle
When I click on that,
the AL view slides over

00:49:11.256 --> 00:49:13.166 A:middle
and I get a list of
the unresolved issues.

00:49:14.096 --> 00:49:16.816 A:middle
Here's telling tell me I have
content priority ambiguity.

00:49:17.016 --> 00:49:21.686 A:middle
All right, and I can find

00:49:21.686 --> 00:49:24.936 A:middle
out what content
priority ambiguity is by--

00:49:25.176 --> 00:49:26.566 A:middle
there we go, clicking
on this button here.

00:49:26.566 --> 00:49:28.636 A:middle
It gives me a detailed
explanation

00:49:28.636 --> 00:49:30.036 A:middle
of content priority ambiguity.

00:49:30.806 --> 00:49:35.726 A:middle
Oh, OK. And here in the second
paragraph, it says to fix,

00:49:35.726 --> 00:49:38.036 A:middle
I need to increase or
decrease the content priority

00:49:38.036 --> 00:49:38.506 A:middle
of my labels.

00:49:38.926 --> 00:49:40.676 A:middle
So, you could think
of content priority

00:49:40.676 --> 00:49:42.886 A:middle
as how strongly a
view wants to remain

00:49:42.886 --> 00:49:44.216 A:middle
at its intrinsic content size?

00:49:44.946 --> 00:49:47.926 A:middle
And in this case, I want my
Name label to get stretched

00:49:47.926 --> 00:49:49.816 A:middle
or clipped more easily
than my Date label.

00:49:50.166 --> 00:49:51.866 A:middle
So, I wanted the content
priority to be lower

00:49:51.866 --> 00:49:53.286 A:middle
than my Date label's
content priority.

00:49:53.736 --> 00:50:01.046 A:middle
If I click on this button
here, it gives me a suggestion

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:49:53.736 --> 00:50:01.046 A:middle
If I click on this button
here, it gives me a suggestion

00:50:01.366 --> 00:50:05.166 A:middle
for how I might want
to fix this issue.

00:50:05.366 --> 00:50:08.876 A:middle
So, it's offering to
decrease the content priority

00:50:08.876 --> 00:50:09.606 A:middle
of my Name label.

00:50:09.896 --> 00:50:11.516 A:middle
And wants it to make--
wants to make it lower

00:50:11.516 --> 00:50:13.836 A:middle
than my Date label's priority,
and that's exactly what I want.

00:50:13.876 --> 00:50:15.466 A:middle
So, I'm just going to
choose Change Priority.

00:50:16.016 --> 00:50:21.546 A:middle
And when I did that, oh, you
can see my labels are no longer

00:50:21.546 --> 00:50:22.296 A:middle
marked as ambiguous.

00:50:22.296 --> 00:50:23.186 A:middle
They have blue constraints.

00:50:23.816 --> 00:50:26.686 A:middle
So, let's hit Build and Run
and take a look at that.

00:50:27.516 --> 00:50:32.266 A:middle
[ Pause ]

00:50:32.766 --> 00:50:33.726 A:middle
OK, there we go.

00:50:33.796 --> 00:50:36.546 A:middle
So now, it's getting clipped
with a little bit of padding,

00:50:36.706 --> 00:50:40.536 A:middle
and it's no longer occluding
that disclosure indicator.

00:50:40.536 --> 00:50:46.756 A:middle
All right, so just saw a couple
different types of ambiguity,

00:50:47.206 --> 00:50:48.916 A:middle
and I showed you a
couple of different ways

00:50:48.916 --> 00:50:50.236 A:middle
to resolve that ambiguity.

00:50:50.556 --> 00:50:52.056 A:middle
There's just one more
feature I'd like to show you

00:50:52.356 --> 00:50:54.436 A:middle
which is useful when you
defined your own custom

00:50:54.436 --> 00:50:56.626 A:middle
controlling code.

00:50:56.686 --> 00:51:00.006 A:middle
And so for this example,
let's imagine that instead

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:50:56.686 --> 00:51:00.006 A:middle
And so for this example,
let's imagine that instead

00:51:00.006 --> 00:51:00.966 A:middle
of this Date label here.

00:51:01.306 --> 00:51:03.626 A:middle
I want to use my own
custom data control

00:51:03.626 --> 00:51:04.656 A:middle
that I've implemented in code.

00:51:05.336 --> 00:51:07.166 A:middle
Actually, I already have a
scene and the story board set

00:51:07.166 --> 00:51:09.396 A:middle
up that way, so I'm going
to scroll over down here.

00:51:09.996 --> 00:51:15.786 A:middle
OK, so this is the exact same
table view only we have replaced

00:51:15.786 --> 00:51:17.556 A:middle
that Date label with UIView,

00:51:17.556 --> 00:51:19.696 A:middle
and that UIView has
its custom class set

00:51:19.696 --> 00:51:22.616 A:middle
to my date control class.

00:51:22.806 --> 00:51:24.516 A:middle
You can see when I select
it, I already have a bunch

00:51:24.516 --> 00:51:26.466 A:middle
of constraints, and I
can get more details

00:51:26.466 --> 00:51:28.446 A:middle
on those constraints in the
size inspector over here.

00:51:29.586 --> 00:51:31.746 A:middle
And in particular, I want to
point out that it has a width

00:51:31.746 --> 00:51:32.466 A:middle
and a height constraint.

00:51:33.536 --> 00:51:36.026 A:middle
So, earlier I mentioned
you don't want to add--

00:51:36.026 --> 00:51:38.176 A:middle
you don't want to add explicit
width or height constraints

00:51:38.406 --> 00:51:40.426 A:middle
to views that define
intrinsic content sizes

00:51:40.466 --> 00:51:43.856 A:middle
because then you risk clipping
or getting somewhere in padding.

00:51:45.046 --> 00:51:47.866 A:middle
And my date control does define
an intrinsic content size.

00:51:49.046 --> 00:51:50.466 A:middle
However, Interface
Builder only knows

00:51:50.466 --> 00:51:53.296 A:middle
about the built-in
system controls.

00:51:53.296 --> 00:51:55.196 A:middle
It doesn't know about this
intrinsic content size

00:51:55.196 --> 00:51:56.236 A:middle
that I have implemented in code.

00:51:57.166 --> 00:52:04.296 A:middle
And when I delete these
height constraints,

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:51:57.166 --> 00:52:04.296 A:middle
And when I delete these
height constraints,

00:52:04.296 --> 00:52:07.176 A:middle
my view is ambiguous because
Interface Builder doesn't have

00:52:07.176 --> 00:52:09.316 A:middle
enough information to know
what it size should be.

00:52:10.566 --> 00:52:12.716 A:middle
So for situations like this
where you know you want

00:52:12.716 --> 00:52:16.356 A:middle
to use information at runtime to
get your intrinsic content size,

00:52:16.926 --> 00:52:19.016 A:middle
you can tell Interface
Builder, it's OK, you don't need

00:52:19.016 --> 00:52:21.936 A:middle
to warn me about an
ambiguous size, and you can do

00:52:21.936 --> 00:52:24.176 A:middle
that by giving in a placeholder
intrinsic content size.

00:52:24.176 --> 00:52:26.636 A:middle
So, I'm going to click on this
button and choose Placeholder.

00:52:27.746 --> 00:52:29.256 A:middle
And now, I've just
told Interface Builder

00:52:29.256 --> 00:52:31.856 A:middle
to use this size as my
intrinsic content size,

00:52:31.856 --> 00:52:33.896 A:middle
and it's OK if I don't have
width or height constraints.

00:52:34.246 --> 00:52:36.286 A:middle
And when I did that,
it's no longer ambiguous.

00:52:36.786 --> 00:52:41.116 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:52:41.616 --> 00:52:43.696 A:middle
All right, so you just saw
a bunch of different ways,

00:52:43.696 --> 00:52:44.846 A:middle
a bunch of different
tools we've added

00:52:44.846 --> 00:52:46.776 A:middle
to help you resolve
Auto Layout issues.

00:52:48.196 --> 00:52:49.816 A:middle
First, you can use
the canvas decorations

00:52:49.876 --> 00:52:52.516 A:middle
to see how your view is
misplaced or ambiguous

00:52:53.326 --> 00:52:56.306 A:middle
or you can get a quick look
at all the unresolved issues

00:52:56.306 --> 00:53:00.156 A:middle
in your document using the mini
navigator, issue navigator.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:52:56.306 --> 00:53:00.156 A:middle
in your document using the mini
navigator, issue navigator.

00:53:00.156 --> 00:53:03.116 A:middle
If you want to quickly
update the constraints

00:53:03.116 --> 00:53:05.006 A:middle
on your misplaced view
or add constraints

00:53:05.006 --> 00:53:09.016 A:middle
to an ambiguous view, you can
use the Canvas Resolving menu

00:53:09.016 --> 00:53:10.086 A:middle
at the bottom of the canvas

00:53:10.626 --> 00:53:13.586 A:middle
or if you want some more
information about your issue,

00:53:13.676 --> 00:53:15.826 A:middle
you can always head over to the
Interface Builder outline view

00:53:15.826 --> 00:53:18.666 A:middle
to get more detailed help.

00:53:18.936 --> 00:53:21.076 A:middle
So, that wraps up
the new workflows

00:53:21.076 --> 00:53:22.216 A:middle
for Auto Layout in Xcode 5.

00:53:23.056 --> 00:53:23.926 A:middle
Before we finish, I just want

00:53:23.926 --> 00:53:25.476 A:middle
to add one quick note
on compatibility.

00:53:26.836 --> 00:53:30.566 A:middle
So all the features we discussed
today are fully compatible

00:53:30.566 --> 00:53:33.696 A:middle
with any previous OS version
that supports Auto Layout,

00:53:34.666 --> 00:53:37.156 A:middle
or we use these great features,
and you'd be using Xcode 5,

00:53:37.876 --> 00:53:40.666 A:middle
and your Interface Builder
document won't be compatible

00:53:40.666 --> 00:53:41.886 A:middle
with previous versions of Xcode.

00:53:42.676 --> 00:53:45.566 A:middle
If you really need your,
[inaudible] story board

00:53:45.566 --> 00:53:47.646 A:middle
to be backwards compatibility,
you can always downgrade it

00:53:47.646 --> 00:53:49.736 A:middle
in the File Inspector, but
then you won't have access

00:53:49.736 --> 00:53:50.436 A:middle
to these features.

00:53:50.946 --> 00:53:55.406 A:middle
And of course and along with
the new Auto Layout workflows

00:53:55.406 --> 00:53:56.716 A:middle
and of course support for iOS 7,

00:53:57.386 --> 00:53:59.396 A:middle
Xcode 5 brings along
a new readable

00:53:59.396 --> 00:54:00.976 A:middle
and diff-able XML
format for this.

